Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with the problem of detecting fluorescent security fibers on identity documents captured under ultraviolet light. This involves image processing and analysis, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves the detection of specific features (fluorescent security fibers) on identity documents, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The use of ultraviolet light to capture images of identity documents can be seen as a form of multimedia processing. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The detection of fluorescent security fibers is a security measure used in identity documents, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The proposed solution involves ridge detection in the gray-scale image of the document with preliminary normalized background, which can be seen as a form of algorithmic approach to the problem.
